  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the other 1/2 of the house was the police department.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we lived in that old house, but our village is-- they established a border, because in 1914, our village was the border between Austria and Russia.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the German kept the same exactly thing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So they brought in, and they-- they established a border.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they brought in a Grenzschitzkommando, like a border patrol, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that patrol, they set up in school.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And every Jewish household is supposed to send somebody to service them-- clean their boots, heat their, you know, they have-- we had to cut the-- cut wood, and so on, and clean the rooms, and so on, and so on, and so on.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was the-- I was only boy in my household.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So my father said, you go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So every day I used to get up in the morning and-- and go there, and spend there maybe four, five hours there, you know, and do casual work, like cut the wood, and-- and clean the rooms, and-- and clean their boots, and all kind of-- that kind of work.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were, at that time, it was more or less, you know, you see, at-- at Berestechko, our-- our part called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Other words, that was Polish occupied-- occupied land.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Berestechko just 5 kilometers from there, was already Russian.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They figured that that's-- there's entirely different-- difference laws, entirely-- they-- they got their ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They build a ghetto right away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they took 'em in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- they murdered the Jews a lot-- six months before they-- we ever had-- had the first actzia, you know?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I remember that commandant from our border patrol came over and he said to me, he says, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
